HEADWORD: Inscribable
<hw>In*scrib"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being inscribed, -- used specif. <fld>(Math.)</fld> of solids or plane
figures capable of being inscribed in other solids or figures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inscribableness</ent>⟦br⟧
